<p>This starts on line 33, so let's run just this scenario:</p>
<pre><code>php vendor/bin/behat features/api/token.feature:33</code></pre>
<p>Oh no, and it actually passes! Instead of the 400 we want, it is giving us
the 201, which means that things are not failing validation. You can see
for the note it says <code>default note</code>. If you look back in our <code>TokenController</code>...
Ah ha! It's because  I forgot to take off the default value. So now it's either
going to be set to whatever the note is or <code>null</code>:</p>
